content.rendered:
You need to know the current Bull Riding Standings WEATHER GUARD® PRCA 2021 World Standings in accordance with the money won during the regular season, the Justin Boots Playoffs and Championships, and for many bull riders, the PRCA Xtreme Bulls Tour.

Watch NFR 2023 Live Online - SUBSCRIBE HERE

NFR 2023 Streaming info
Streaming
The Cowboy Channel (real-time) Watch Here
RFD-TV (real-time) Watch Here
Cowboy Channel Plus (International) Watch Here

 

Sage Kimzey has been so consistent for the past six years when it comes to ProRodeo Bull Riding since he has won it all. We also expect 2021 to be no different, and he might win the seventh straight title as Kimzey remains the king of PRCA Bull Riders.

Kimzey has held the top spot, and currently, his standings are over $92,000 for the 2021 Wrangler NFR. However, there was a time two young bull riders were reigning as the best with No.1 ranking this year. They are 20-year-old Ky Hamilton, currently ranked as No.2, and 22-year-old Boudreaux Campbell, currently rated as No. 3.
